        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>mineral [300011068], inorganic material [300010360], materials by composition [300212963], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Multi-colored transparent or translucent material containing calcium fluoride, commonly occurring in massive crystalline cube form with perfect octahedral cleavage, used as flux, as a source of fluoride compound, and in the preparation of opalescent and opaque glass, vitreous enamel, and a purple pigment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079379/National Gallery, London [online] (2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Material transparente o translúcido multicolor que contiene fluoruro de calcio, que se presenta comúnmente en forma de un cubo cristalino masivo con una descomposición perfecta octaédrica, utilizado como fundente, como fuente de compuestos de fluoruros y en la preparación de vidrio opalescente y opaco y de esmalte vítreo.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Veelkleurig doorzichtig of doorschijnend materiaal dat calciumfluoride bevat; het komt over het algemeen voor in de vorm van massieve kristallijne kubussen met perfecte octaëdrische splijtingen. Het wordt gebruikt als vloeimiddel, als bron voor fluorideverbindingen en bij het maken van glas met opaalweerschijn en email.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>多色的透明或半透明物質，含有氟化鈣，通常以具有完美八面體解理的塊狀結晶立方體存在，被用來做助熔劑、氟化物的來源以及製備乳光玻璃、不透明玻璃和玻璃琺瑯。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
